306
00:16:00,860 --> 00:16:02,460
What's the matter?

307
00:16:02,460 --> 00:16:06,160
It seems you poked your finger with something and got hurt.

308
00:16:07,160 --> 00:16:08,860
Oh, I get it!

309
00:16:08,860 --> 00:16:11,760
When you put your handkerchief back in your pocket a while ago,

310
00:16:11,760 --> 00:16:13,660
you seemed to be in pain, right?

311
00:16:14,760 --> 00:16:16,960
You've got something in your pocket, don't you?

312
00:16:16,960 --> 00:16:18,660
Won't you please show it to us?

313
00:16:18,660 --> 00:16:19,960
The contents in his pocket

314
00:16:19,960 --> 00:16:24,360
is probably a thumbtack or something stuck onto a tape

315
00:16:24,360 --> 00:16:26,660
with the blood stain of the on it.

316
00:16:26,660 --> 00:16:29,060
Oh, how do you know?

317
00:16:29,060 --> 00:16:31,160
Just by looking at the slight snatches of blood stains

318
00:16:31,160 --> 00:16:33,060
that are that are splattered on the bookshelf.

319
00:16:33,060 --> 00:16:36,660
It is obvious that something had been stuck on here.

320
00:16:36,660 --> 00:16:39,060
You adjusted the direction of the thumbtack

321
00:16:39,060 --> 00:16:40,960
and stuck it on to the bookshelf.

322
00:16:40,960 --> 00:16:43,260
Then, you hooked the loop of the string on,

